31/03/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The government approved an anti-corruption strategy Wednesday (30 March) that requires the strict screening of employees appointed to institutions with a high risk of corruption, such as the ministries of finance, interior and healthcare. 
The cabinet also approved the judicial reform strategy for 2005-2007, which envisions upgrading legislation to guarantee the independence of prosecutors. 
It also gives them the right to complain if their superiors interfere in probes. 
(Rompres, Nine o'clock - 31/03/05)
